  53.4.10 ESMF_UtilStringInt2String - convert integer to character string

   INTERFACE:
     function ESMF_UtilStringInt2String (i, rc)

   ARGUMENTS:
       integer, intent(in) :: i
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
       integer, intent(out), optional  :: rc

   RETURN VALUE:
       character(int2str_len (i)) :: ESMF_UtilStringInt2String

   DESCRIPTION:

   Converts given an integer to string representation. The returned string
   is sized such that it does not contain leading or trailing blanks.

   This procedure may fail when used in an expression in a write statement
   with some older, pre-Fortran 2003, compiler environments that do not
   support re-entrant I/O calls.

   The arguments are:

   i
          An integer.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

